Real-time endpoints in Azure ML require a scoring script with `init()` and `run(raw_data)`. For example:

```python
import joblib

def init():
    global model
    model = joblib.load('model.joblib')

def run(data):
    return model.predict(data)
```

Read more in the [official documentation](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/machine-learning/how-to-deploy-model-custom-entry-script?view=azureml-api-2).
